projects.description:
KPN Internedservices (KIS) is a cloud hosting provider and a subsidiary of KPN. 
KIS wants to be more data driven and together with KPN ICT Consulting a project was set up to discover the possibilities. After a succesful Proof of Concept predicting the Net Promoter Score (NPS) a project of six months was started. During these six months several solutions were implemented such as a churn prediction, new SLA reporting and KPI dashboards. The way of working was by means of Scrum with sprints of 4 weeks. The employees of KIS also received training to be able to make their own dashboards. Python was used to do the analyses, in combination with displaying the results in Microsoft PowerBI using a connection with an Azure Database where all the data was stored.

Responsibilities:
•	Business analysis on requirements to make the client more data driven;
•	Feature engineering;
•	Feature selection;
•	Building (mathematical) models;
•	Visualizing the data in a product that is clear to the customer using Power BI.

Result:
☑ Working Data Lake with a connection to several databases.
☑ Several PowerBI dashboards.
☑ NPS prediction model & churn prediction model.
☑ Increased NPS of the client.

All KPN services are monitored 24/7 by SQC, including the IMS service. Anomaly detection analyse was performed to identify deviations. The trend of different KPIs over time are mapped to perform predictions. Based on these predictions and calculated limits an alarm is generated if there is possible impact on the service. A system was built that automatically sends these alarms to the SQC in case of deviant behavior so that they can act on it.

Responsibilities:
•	Project Management;
•	Stakeholder management;
•	Documentation;
•	Creating a working prediction model in R;
•	Creating a working integral alarm system on hadoop.

Result:
Working R scripts which:
☑ Predicts the IMS KPI's based on historical data;
☑ Sets limits for deviant behavior;
☑ Generates alarms in form of csv files;
☑ Connects with Hadoop platform to provide an operational system.

This way the operators at SQC don't have to check every individual graph, which gives them more time to investigate anomalies. 
Also determing anomalies is not reliant anymore on the experience of the operators.

Royal IHC migrated all her worksplaces to Office 365. KPN ICT Consulting supported this migration with a team that took the technical aspects under control, this way the ICT department of IHC did not need to worry about this.

Responsibilities: 
•	Completing all steps to perform migrations to Office 365;
•	Project planning;
•	Transfering knowledge;
•	Ad-hoc problem solving regarding the migration requiring technical know-how.

Result:
Succesfully migrated a large amount of Business Units to Office 365. 
Mapped the processes of the migration and developed a manual for future migration consultants.
